Fourteen men accused of hacking a man to death in Marikana in the North West will appear in the Rustenburg Magistrate s Court on Monday. The 14, including activist Napoleon Webster, were arrested following the murder of Sabata Petrus Chale in Marikana West in December last year. Aubrey Seitsang, Sibonile Sobopha, Mdlondozi Fundiwo, Herbert Baqhesi, Napoleon Webster, and William Nyenyane have already been denied bail. Aphndile Pungone, Samson Gqwetani, Gift Luveli, Nkululeko Msithwa, Nkosindiphile Nziyose, Luvo Soyizwaphi, Sivuyile Qasha, and Mzolisi Mbulana are expected to apply for bail on Monday. The State alleges they hacked Chale, 39, to death on December 8, 2016, allegedly over the allocation of low cost (RDP) houses at Marikana West Extension 2. Chale was allegedly chased by a group of about 30 people and was hacked to death with pangas, axes, and spears. He died at the scene. His attackers allegedly drank his blood. African News Agency (ANA)